Right Said Manfred

John Ourand: Give me a quick report card for the first half of the season.

Rob Manfred: Our focus going into the year was to maintain our momentum fro=
m last year. The idea that we=E2=80=99re running a little bit ahead of the =
70 million pace for attendance is a big deal for us and is really important=
 in terms of continuing to build excitement around the sport.

You added the pitch clock and got rid of the defensive shift. What other ch=
anges would you like to see?

Even with respect to the pitch clock this year, we made little changes in a=
n effort to make sure that we didn=E2=80=99t backslide. [Ed note: Pitchers =
now have 18 seconds to throw a pitch with runners on base, down from last s=
eason=E2=80=99s 20 seconds.] In fact, our game times are actually down a li=
ttle bit from last year=E2=80=99s numbers by two
minutes=E2=80=94and down 34 minutes from 2021. That=E2=80=99s important. Ou=
r number one priority is to make sure that we don=E2=80=99t give up ground =
on areas where we=E2=80=99ve made important progress. Given the history and=
 tradition of our game, it=E2=80=99s important to make sure that you make c=
hanges when they=E2=80=99re really necessary. So we=E2=80=99re going to con=
tinue to monitor those developments.

What else can we expect to see?

I=E2=80=99m not committed to making any additional changes right now. I thi=
nk that we had a lot of change. We need to make sure that we maintain the g=
round and watch developments in the game to determine if it=E2=80=99s neces=
sary to make additional changes. That said, we are a little concerned about=
 offense, and we=E2=80=99re looking hard at the offense numbers in the game=
=2E We=E2=80=99ll continue to do that.

My friends keep complaining that the sport is too old and it=E2=80=99s hard=
 to get their kids interested in baseball.

Our sport gets a bad rap on that
one. The 18-to-34 demo on our national TV broadcasts is up 20 percent this =
year. That=E2=80=99s a great number for us and part of a larger trend. Our =
ticket buyers are getting younger=E2=80=94the median age has moved down by =
seven years. All of those indicators are really important for us in terms o=
f making the game younger.

As an Orioles fan, I=E2=80=99ve watched games this season on Roku, Apple TV=
+, ESPN, Fox, and MASN. Is this a problem?

I don=E2=80=99t think we would be on as many platforms as we=E2=80=99re on =
right now if we were not experimenting and trying to find the best path for=
ward in a really unstable media environment. Ideally, I would like to be on=
 a smaller number of platforms to put our brands in a position where there=
=E2=80=99s a go-to spot where you always know you can find your games. And =
if it isn=E2=80=99t there, it=E2=80=99s clearly referenced where it=E2=80=
=99s available.

From the Cheap Seats

On how Fox Sports makes money in soccer: =E2=80=9CTypically, Fox Sports beg=
ins its program match rating for soccer events, like the Copa and Euro Cham=
pionship, before the matches start, during their pre-match coverage. As suc=
h, they can sell that inventory at in-match rates. This helps monetize the =
properties. Of course, the Euro Championship has affiliate fee value, so th=
ey make money there as well (not so much Copa America).=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A=
 former Fox Sports executive

On Fox=E2=80=99s Euro and Copa coverage: =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s an abominati=
on that Fox Sports would not provide an upconverted 4K HDR feed of their tw=
o major soccer finals. I hear the concerns from broadcast affiliate ownersh=
ip groups who get upset about 4K simulcast channels not having their local =
ad inventory, but fans being forced to watch =E2=80=99the world=E2=80=99s g=
reatest events on
Fox=E2=80=99 in legacy 720p video quality is criminal in 2024.=E2=80=9D =E2=
=80=94A digital content and social media executive and self-described =E2=
=80=9C35-Year Pay TV Subscriber & Soccer Snob=E2=80=9D

On my story about Charter=E2=80=99s Spectrum subscribers not downloading Di=
sney+ or ESPN+: =E2=80=9CNo way it=E2=80=99s being widely adopted with what=
 we assume is an aging customer base who presumably fit into the =E2=80=98d=
on=E2=80=99t like change=E2=80=99 demographic. Spectrum was trying to get a=
ttention during their Disney/ESPN/ABC dispute, and it worked. The problem i=
s, Spectrum did nothing to solve the primary consumer issue=E2=80=A6 consum=
ers want the 30 core sports/entertainment channels=E2=80=94none of the reru=
n catalog channels, and none of the channels which have just two original p=
rograms. Most consumers didn=E2=80=99t want streaming services included wit=
h their cable bundle=E2=80=A6 and they do not want to pay more than $44.99 =
per month to receive them. I performed many roles at Time Warner Cable for =
over a decade, and the one
common thing with consumers [was]=E2=80=94=E2=80=98I need to lower my month=
ly bill, but I also don=E2=80=99t want to remove any of my existing channel=
s.=E2=80=99 The idea of Spulu is what people want, but it doesn=E2=80=99t h=
ave all the required pieces at the right price. The same problem as everyon=
e else.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A former cable guy, via X ( https://x.com/7075WxS=
potter/status/1813230780086198765?utm_campaign=3DThe+Varsity+-+SUBSCRIBERS+=
%287%2F18%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Varsity+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%286%2F6%2F24%29&=
utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42a=
bd12a )

On NBA rights: =E2=80=9CAny word on the distribution of League Pass in the =
new NBA media deal? Will it be exclusively available on one platform or ava=
ilable widely like it is today?=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A media executive

[Ed note: All signs suggest that the NBA=E2=80=99s out-of-market League Pas=
