          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px;">
           <p style=3D"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 30px; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0;">Welcome back to The Varsity=
, my twice-weekly private email on the sports media industrial complex=E2=
=80=94the moneybags, power players, egomaniacs, and the genuinely nice peop=
le sprinkled in among them. Happy British Open Day to all who celebrate.<br=
/><br/>Since I spent the early part of this week attending MLB=E2=80=99s Al=
l-Star Game festivities, this private email is chock-full of items I picked=
 up in Dallas-Fort Worth, including a readout of my informative chat with c=
ommissioner <b>Rob Manfred</b> regarding the state of his league. I also sp=
ent time in Dallas reporting on the NBA rights auction, since we have, <i>m=
ercifully</i>, entered the <i>five-day window </i>in which <b>David Zaslav<=
/b>=E2=80=99s Warner Bros. Discovery can exercise its <i>matching rights</i=
>. Yes, yes, I know that <i>matching rights </i>have become The Varsity=E2=
=80=99s favorite new drinking game, forcing
my well-heeled readership to knock back a sip upon every mention as they on=
ce did for <i>cliff path</i>, <i>glide path</i>, etcetera. Don=E2=80=99t bl=
ame the messenger: Now, drink!<br/><br/>Speaking of which=E2=80=A6 for thos=
e getting caught with their hand in the cookie jar, this is the <i>last cal=
l</i> to stop forwarding this private email to your colleagues and pals who=
 should be paying full freight. <u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/e=
yJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dReUdWZldXX3NIaUQwalk3a3gtYz0iLCJo=
