          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;"><b><i>John Ourand</=
i>: Give me a quick report card for the first half of the season.</b><br/><=
br/><i>Rob Manfred</i>: Our focus going into the year was to maintain our m=
omentum from last year. The idea that we=E2=80=99re running a little bit ah=
ead of the 70 million pace for attendance is a big deal for us and is reall=
y important in terms of continuing to build excitement around the sport.<br=
/><br/><b>You added the pitch clock and got rid of the defensive shift. Wha=
t other changes would you like to see?</b><br/><br/>Even with respect to th=
e pitch clock this year, we made little changes in an effort to make sure t=
hat we didn=E2=80=99t backslide. [<i>Ed note</i>: Pitchers now have 18 seco=
nds to throw a pitch with runners on base, down from last season=E2=80=99s =
20 seconds.] In fact, our game times are actually down a little bit from la=
st year=E2=80=99s numbers by two
minutes=E2=80=94and down 34 minutes from 2021. That=E2=80=99s important. Ou=
r number one priority is to make sure that we don=E2=80=99t give up ground =
on areas where we=E2=80=99ve made important progress. Given the history and=
 tradition of our game, it=E2=80=99s important to make sure that you make c=
hanges when they=E2=80=99re really necessary. So we=E2=80=99re going to con=
tinue to monitor those developments.  <br/><br/><b>What else can we expect =
to see?</b><br/><br/>I=E2=80=99m not committed to making any additional cha=
nges right now. I think that we had a lot of change. We need to make sure t=
hat we maintain the ground and watch developments in the game to determine =
if it=E2=80=99s necessary to make additional changes. That said, we are a l=
ittle concerned about offense, and we=E2=80=99re looking hard at the offens=
e numbers in the game. We=E2=80=99ll continue to do that.<br/><br/><b>My fr=
iends keep complaining that the sport is too old and it=E2=80=99s hard to g=
et their kids interested in baseball.</b><br/><br/>Our sport gets a bad rap=
 on that
one. The 18-to-34 demo on our national TV broadcasts is up 20 percent this =
year. That=E2=80=99s a great number for us and part of a larger trend. Our =
ticket buyers are getting younger=E2=80=94the median age has moved down by =
seven years. All of those indicators are really important for us in terms o=
f making the game younger.<br/><br/><b>As an Orioles fan, I=E2=80=99ve watc=
hed games this season on Roku, Apple TV+, ESPN, Fox, and MASN. Is this a pr=
oblem?</b><br/><br/>I don=E2=80=99t think we would be on as many platforms =
as we=E2=80=99re on right now if we were not experimenting and trying to fi=
nd the best path forward in a really unstable media environment. Ideally, I=
 would like to be on a smaller number of platforms to put our brands in a p=
osition where there=E2=80=99s a go-to spot where you always know you can fi=
nd your games. And if it isn=E2=80=99t there, it=E2=80=99s clearly referenc=
ed where it=E2=80=99s available. <br/></td>
